Paper: hep-th/9507092

Date: 1995-07-18

Title: An elegant solution of the n-body Toda problem

Comments: LaTeX, 13 pp

Journal-ref: J.Math.Phys. 37 (1996) 1349-1355

The solution of the classical open-chain n-body Toda problem is derived froman ansatz and is found to have a highly symmetric form. The proof requires anunusual identity involving Vandermonde determinants. The explicittransformation to action-angle variables is exhibited.